title: Capital Hill 1 Bdrm/Studio Unit
map_address: Harvard Ave E near E Olive Way
posting_body: ['Coming in mid to late August.', 'A spacious and open ground floor apartment.', 'This unit features wall-to-wall carpet, newly remodeled kitchen with plenty of counter space.', 'While the bedroom in this apartment is on the smaller side (full-size-bed), as was common for the time period, the unit itself is very spacious.', 'A small Monthly Fee of $65.00 per person covers the Water, Sewer and Garbage.', 'For the security and safety of our residents, this is a non-smoking building.', 'You must be a NON Smoker to apply, meaning you cannot smoke anything, Pot, Vape, E-cigs, cigs, etc.12-Month Lease', 'Apologies, at this time we are unable to accommodate pets.', 'To schedule a viewing call Darrell:', 'show contact info', '.', "The Harvard Crest is a classic Seattle vintage building, built in the early 1900's.", 'The building is controlled access, with 34 one-bedroom and studio units.', "Many of the kitchens still feature their original iceboxes, used as cabinets today, giving the apartment an old-world charm that's hard to come by now-a-days.", "With an impressive Walk Score of 98, the Harvard Crest is conveniently located just 1 block away from one of Seattle's richest, most diverse streets: Broadway.", "Full of colleges, museums, restaurants, and cool hole-in-the-wall shops, you'll only find here.", 'https://youtu.be/ko3Xhxm7eAE']
